Our world is a big place, but it can often feel quite small. It’s such a vast planet that we would need several lifetimes to be able to see every corner of it! But it’s small enough for us to fit some of the greatest nature reserves on all seven continents onto one amazing livestream. Live: International Day for Biological Diversity – Seven Continents One Home May 22, the International Day for Biological Diversity, come and join us at 10:30 a.m .BJT (2:30 a.m. GMT), as we have an adventure with the wild animals and plants from all around our vast and amazing planet. For more: International Day for Biological Diversity: If they're gone Live: International Day for Biological Diversity - Get close to the urban jungles Live: International Day for Biological Diversity - Learn more about the missed and missing species (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)